law.text:
A petition for administration of a small estate may be filed by any person entitled to administration pursuant to § 5-104 of this title and shall contain, in addition to the information required by §§ 5-201 and 5-202 of this title:
A statement that the petitioner has made a diligent search to discover all property and debts of the decedent;
A list of the known property and its value;
A list of the known creditors of the decedent, with the amount of each claim, including contingent and disputed claims;
A statement of any legal proceedings pending in which the decedent was a party.
